  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nIt's unclear to me if this is a bug or intended behavior, but it is strange and it could affect Gnosis upcoming merge.\r\n\r\nCurrently, on xDai/Gnosis, Nethermind does not return a `nonce` field in the body of the response to `eth_getBlockByNumber`\r\n\r\nOn PoA networks this value is static, at `0x0000000000000000` (or it's `null`? Unclear) so I kind of understand why it's not returned on Gnosis.\r\n\r\nHowever, on PoS networks it is ALSO set to `0x0000000000000000` and Nethermind does return it in the same request on Ropsten.\r\n\r\nSo, really, I think the \"bug\" is that Nethermind should return the `nonce` field in the block data, and it should be set to `0x0000000000000000`?\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\nCall `eth_getBlockByNumber` on a PoA chain, no `nonce` is returned.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nI would expect a `nonce` field to always exist in the response data, regardless of PoW, PoS, or PoA consensus.",
